    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-10-25T15:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-10-25T15:30:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <head>405. Memorandum of telephone conversation between <persName corresp="#p_BM_1"
                        >McGeorge Bundy</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName>,
                    October 25<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d405fn1">Changes in draft message to
                            <persName corresp="#p_TU_1">U Thant</persName>. No classification
                        marking. 1 p. <gloss target="#t_DOS_1">DOS</gloss>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> Papers: Lot 74 D 272,
                        Telcons—Cuba.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-10-25T15:30:00">October 25, 1962, 3:30
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d405-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d405-1"/>
                <p>Bundy—The President has now seen your exact text and he points out that the first
                    clause of paragraph three: “In order to give the parties time” may look as if we
                    were willing to accept a pause at this stage, which we are really not, unless we
                    have a whole lot more in it. Can’t we just leave that out?</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName>—Sure.</p>
                <p>Bundy—“In your statement you have made, your message makes certain suggestions,
                    you have invited preliminary talks and I’ve been” perhaps those two paragraphs
                    could be collapsed together.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName>—Right.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
